section.section:
The Scenic and Wild Rivers Review Board shall select the members of each local advisory board as follows:
At least 2 members shall own land contiguous to the scenic or wild river, except for the Youghiogheny River where at least 3 members shall own land contiguous to that portion of the river designated by § 8-408(a) of this subtitle as a wild river;
At least 2 members who own land that is not contiguous to the scenic or wild river;
1 member shall represent the local governing body; and
2 members from the county soil conservation district.

text.section:
If a scenic or wild river flows through more than 1 county, the local advisory board shall consist of no more than the following members:
2 residents of each county through which the scenic or wild river flows who own land contiguous to the scenic or wild river;
2 residents of each county through which the scenic or wild river flows who do not own land contiguous to the scenic or wild river;
2 representatives of the local governing body of each county through which the scenic or wild river flows; and
1 representative of each soil conservation district through which the scenic or wild river flows.

Each local scenic and wild river advisory board shall:
Review any inventory, study, plan, and regulation that is proposed under this subtitle and is applicable to any river in its jurisdiction;
Make recommendations on the inventory, study, plan, and regulation to its local governing body and to the Scenic and Wild Rivers Review Board;
Select its own chairperson; and
Adopt its own administrative regulations for the operation of the local advisory board.
